object: Yorkton is a city located in south-eastern Saskatchewan, Canada, about 600 km north-west of Winnipeg and 300 km south-east of Saskatoon.As of 2011 the census population of the city was 15,669.  Yorkton has had a growth rate of 4.2% since 2006.Yorkton was founded in 1882 and incorporated as a city in 1928.  The city is bordered by the RM of Orkney No. 244 to the west and the RM of Wallace No. 243 on the east.
